# Rule 5 — Testing

**No merge until green.** Every feature follows this gate — no exceptions for “small” changes.

```text
Every feature
        ↓
Unit Test
        ↓
Integration Test
        ↓
PHPStan
        ↓
PHPCS
        ↓
Green → only then done / merge-ready
```

## 1. Unit test

- Cover the new/changed public behavior in isolation.
- Location: `packages/<name>/tests/Unit/` (or existing package test layout + Phase 12 Unit folder).
- No full WordPress boot when avoidable.

## 2. Integration test

- Cover the feature across collaborators (provider boot, registry+types, controller+resource, save pipeline, etc.).
- Location: `packages/<name>/tests/Integration/` (or package integration tests).
- Critical path must be green.

## 3. PHPStan

```bash
php composer.phar phpstan
```

Fix every error. Do not hide real issues with ignore comments.

## 4. PHPCS

```bash
php composer.phar phpcs
```

PSR-12 must pass. Fix formatting/structure findings.

## Preferred one-shot

```bash
php composer.phar ci
# = PHPStan → PHPCS → PHPUnit
```

Also run the package suite when scoped:

```bash
php composer.phar test:<package>
```

## Phase 12 (every package, ongoing)

Beyond Unit + Integration, packages keep the five-layer gate green:

```text
Unit → Integration → WordPress → Performance → Security
```

Contract: `packages/TESTING.md` · matrix: `tests/Phase12/MatrixComplianceTest.php`  
`php composer.phar test:phase12`

## Definition of done

| Check | Required |
| ----- | -------- |
| Unit tests for the feature | ✅ |
| Integration tests for the feature | ✅ |
| PHPStan clean | ✅ |
| PHPCS clean | ✅ |
| PHPUnit (affected / `ci`) green | ✅ |

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ “Tests later” / merge with red CI  
- ❌ Only manual smoke, no PHPUnit  
- ❌ PHPStan/PHPCS skipped because “types are obvious”  
- ❌ Claiming a package complete while Phase 12 layers are missing  

**Red CI = not merge-ready. Fix first.**
